It showing that arima (1,1,2) returns the smallest aic value, should be the model to fit.

Running auto-arima

auto.arima(diff(confirmed_Hubei),trace=TRUE)

tsdiag(arima(diff(confirmed_Hubei), order = c(1, 1, 2), include.mean = FALSE))

qqnorm(residuals(arima(diff(confirmed_Hubei), order = c(1, 1, 3), include.mean = FALSE)));qqline(residuals(arima(diff(confirmed_Hubei), order = c(1, 1, 3), include.mean = FALSE)))

arima_confirmed = arima(diff(confirmed_Hubei), order = c(1, 1, 2), include.mean = FALSE)
arima_confirmed_res_square = arima_confirmed$residuals^2
par(mfcol= c(3,1))
plot(arima_confirmed_res_square, main = "Squared Residuals")
acf_confirmed_squared = acf(arima_confirmed_res_square, main = "ACF Squared Residuals")
pacf_confirmed_squared = pacf(arima_confirmed_res_square, main = "PACF Squared Residuals")

fit = auto.arima(diff(confirmed_Hubei), seasonal = FALSE)
tsdisplay(residuals(fit), lag.max=45, main='(2,1,0) Model Residuals')

## Using auto arima model for the forecasting of next 10 days

fcast = forecast(fit,h=10)
par(bg = "black")
plot(fcast, main = "Forecast (Next 10 days) Confirmed Cases in Hubei,China", ylab = "Confirmed Cases", xlab = "Days",
col="white", col.main="white",col.lab="white")
axis(1, col="grey", col.ticks="grey", col.axis="white")
axis(2, col="grey", col.ticks="grey", col.axis="white")

## Forecasting for cofirmed cases in China in the next 10 days

fcast = forecast(fit,h=10)
par(bg = "black")
